            <fr:title text="Spectral spaces">Spectral spaces</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  A topological space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>locally spectral</html:em>, if
  <html:ol><html:li>It is <fr:link href="/topl-FII1/" title="Sober spaces" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/topl-FII1/" display-uri="topl-FII1" type="local">sober</fr:link>.</html:li>
    <html:li>It is <fr:link href="/topl-GW93/" title="Quasi-separated spaces" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/topl-GW93/" display-uri="topl-GW93" type="local">quasi-separated</fr:link>.</html:li>
    <html:li>Compact opens form a basis of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol></html:p>
            <html:p>
  We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>spectral</html:em> if furthermore <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is compact.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
